Recipients' use of disclosed information is not covered by this Privacy Policy. For questions about third-party processing, review their privacy policies.
Social Sharing Features
The App may offer social sharing features, such as the Facebook "Like" button, which let you share actions taken in the App with other media. You must be over the minimum age limit prescribed by legislation to use these features. Sharing information with your friends or the public depends on your settings with the social sharing feature provider.
Children
Use of the App is limited to users aged 13 years and above, except in the European Economic Area, where the limit is 16 years and above. By accepting this Privacy Policy and using the App, you warrant that you meet the applicable age requirement. For additional questions about 24 HIT Riga SIA's privacy practices related to children under the minimum age, contact us at support@24hit-riga.games.
Transfer to Third Countries
In certain circumstances, we transfer your personal data to recipients outside the EEU. These transfers occur only to entities that provide appropriate safeguards to ensure data protection levels in agreement with this Privacy Policy and applicable law. Transfers will be based on:
Privacy Shield Certification
: Entities certified under the US-EU Privacy Shield Framework.
Standard Data Protection Clauses
: Adopted by the European Commission.
Security
24 HIT Riga SIA takes reasonable measures to protect information from loss, theft, misuse, unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, and destruction.
Push Notifications
We send push notifications or alerts to your mobile device for game-related information, service updates, promotional communications, and other messages if you have agreed to such notifications. You can deactivate notifications by changing your device settings.
Selling of Personal Data
24 HIT Riga SIA does not sell your personal data for money. However, we disclose some categories of personal data to third parties for business purposes. If this is interpreted as a "sale" under the CCPA, contact us at support@24hit-riga.games to withdraw your consent.
Your Rights
Rights of EEU Residents
We process and answer requests within one month unless a longer period is required due to complexity, in which case our response time can be up to three months.
Right to Request Access
: You can request access to the data we process about you, including purposes, categories of data, recipients, and storage periods. You can obtain a copy of the data being processed, subject to intellectual property or trade secret restrictions.
Right to Object
: You can object to our processing of your personal data based on the balancing-of-interest rule (Article 6(1)(f) of the GDPR). We will cease processing unless there are compelling legitimate grounds or if necessary for legal claims.
Right to Rectification
: You can request inaccurate personal data to be corrected (Article 16 of the GDPR).
Right to Restriction
: You can request restriction of processing in certain circumstances (Article 18 of the GDPR).
Right to Withdraw Consent
: If we process data based on your consent, you can withdraw consent at any time, affecting future processing.
Right to Data Portability
: You can receive your personal data in a structured, commonly used, machine-readable format and have it transmitted to another data controller without hindrance.
Right to Erasure
: You can request the deletion of your personal data, but deletion is not possible if necessary for legal claims or storage is required by law.
To exercise your rights, contact us at support@24hit-riga.games. You can file complaints with the relevant data protection authorities.
Rights of California Residents
Under the CCPA, California residents have the following rights:
Right to Know
: You can request information about the personal data we have collected about you in the past 12 months.
Right to Delete
: You can request the deletion of your personal data, subject to legal obligations or our need to complete a transaction or provide services.
Right to Opt-Out of Sale
: You can opt-out of the sale of your personal data. 24 HIT Riga SIA does not sell personal data as defined in the CCPA.
To exercise these rights, contact us at support@24hit-riga.games. You can also designate an authorized agent to make these requests on your behalf, but you will need to verify your identity with us directly.
